DURBAN - The Department of Home Affairs have speeded up the process which has allowed Bafana Bafana midfielder Kamohelo Mokotjo to be granted his South African citizenship ahead of the international friendlies against Guinea-Bissau and Angola.READ: Bafana beat Guinea-BissauMokotjo renounced his birth nationality when he became a Dutch citizen last December which meant he was unable to represent the national team.He had made appearances for Bafana and the junior national teams.READ: Bafana quartet doubtful for Angola friendlyAfter the Department of Home Affairs were eventually called in to try and fast-track the process, the minister approving Mokotjo s urgent application to reacquire his SA nationality in time for Saturday s match with Guinea-Bissau in Durban. The Minister of Home Affairs, Malusi Gigaba, has, by the power vested in terms of Section 13(3)(a)(i) of the South African Citizenship Act, 1995 (Act No. 88 of 1995), allowed Kamohelo Mokotjo to resume his former South African citizenship, confirmed a statement released by Home Affairs on Friday.READ: Bafana seek passionate support in East London Mokotjo acquired Dutch citizenship in December 2016 and automatically lost his South African citizenship. The Minister approved the application after carefully applying his mind to a motivation submitted before him by the applicant stating the reasons for the request.African News Agency